Bidvest, Mercantile Shares May Move: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-07-06T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/bidvest-mercantile-bank-may-move-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell for the first day
in nine, dropping 123.53, or 0.4 percent, to 32,130.71 in
Johannesburg.        Bidvest Group Ltd. (BVT)  : The diversified management
company’s offer to buy  Mercantile Bank Holdings Ltd. (MTL)  was
rejected by Caixa Geral de Depositos SA’s board, the Portuguese
bank said in an e-mailed statement. Bidvest shares rose 7.46
rand, or 4.8 percent, to 162 rand.  Mercantile Bank Holdings Ltd. (MTL SJ): The lender’s stock
has remained unchanged since July 4 at 31 cents a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen in  Cape Town  at 
